        <abstract>
            <p>Explains how melting of ice in Glen Spean could have successively freed two lower cols, thus establishing the water-levels that determined the two lower shelves in Glen Roy.</p> 
<p>Plans to read a paper to the Linnean Society ["Sexual forms of <hi rend="italic">Catasetum</hi>", <hi rend="italic">Collected papers</hi> 2: 63–70].</p> 
